This paper deals with optimizing the performance of Wi-Fi networks, which falls under the category of computer networks (cs.NI). The proposed method uses deep reinforcement learning principles, which is a popular area of research in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the efficiency and computational cost of the proposed method, which relates to systems and control (cs.SY) and information theory (cs.IT).
